                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d834">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">390.115A/1489: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harrison</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-03-16">March 16,
                            1943</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>638. Your 1552, March 7th.<note n="25" xml:id="d834fn25">Not printed.</note>
                    American interests, Japan. Swiss should request Japanese authorities to install
                    a canteen at Negishi Yokohama Camp in accordance with the provisions of Article
                    12 of the Geneva Prisoners of War Convention.</p>
                <p>The attention of the Swiss authorities should be again drawn to paragraph 2 of
                    Department’s 393 of February 15<note n="26" xml:id="d834fn26">
                        <hi rend="italic">Post</hi>, <ref target="#pg_1015">p. 1015</ref>.</note>
                    with regard to interviews between internees and Swiss delegate in the presence
                    of witnesses.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
